  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess the effectivity of using hypertonic nasal solutions
      alone on the symptom scores and nasal eosinophil levels of allergic rhinitis patients,
      retrospectively.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The medical records of the patients who admitted to outpatient clinic of otorhinolaryngology
      department of a tertiary referral center were retrospectively investigated. The symptom
      scores and nasal eosinophil levels of the patients were recorded. Patients using hypertonic
      solutions alone or steroid nasal spray alone were compared.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
